<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="594" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1039,2037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,316,1293,1317]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="594" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1293,1317]" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick, 1926" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1926" box="[635,917,1293,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nausicaa">
<emphasis box="[635,756,1294,1317]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">P. nausicaa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick, E." box="[761,917,1293,1317]" pageId="4" pageNumber="594" refId="ref3568" refString="Meyrick, E. (1926) Exotic Microlepidoptera. Vol. 3. Marlborough, Wilts, 640 pp." type="book" year="1926">
Meyrick, 
<quantity box="[864,917,1293,1317]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.89204" pageId="4" pageNumber="594" unit="in" value="1926.0">1926</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the forewing pattern with pale-orange to lightyellow blotch, but it can be distinguished from the latter by the forewing being more elongated, and having a larger, elongate-quadrate yellowish patch, whereas the patch in the forewing is much shorter and more or less ovate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1926" box="[1297,1419,1366,1389]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nausicaa">
<emphasis box="[1297,1419,1366,1389]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">P. nausicaa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="595" pageId="4" pageNumber="594" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1039,2037]" box="[199,835,1401,1425]" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,338,1401,1425]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="594" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,1401,1425]" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Male (
<figureCitation box="[414,486,1401,1425]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,244,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,642,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-232@5.[157,1431,633,1907]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Ptilothyris galbiplatella Park, sp. nov.: A, adult, holotype; B, antenna; C, labial palpi, lateral view; D, male genitalia, gen. slide no. CIS-7114; E, ditto, aedeagus; F, aedeagus of the paratype; G, close-up juxta of the paratype, CIS-7113; H, abdominal segments VI–VIII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529781/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
A–C). Wingspan 18.0–19.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1039,2037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,257,1437,1461]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">Head</emphasis>
: Dark purplish brown dorsal surface; yellowish orange on face. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[1061,1144,1437,1461]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,244,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,642,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-232@5.[157,1431,633,1907]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Ptilothyris galbiplatella Park, sp. nov.: A, adult, holotype; B, antenna; C, labial palpi, lateral view; D, male genitalia, gen. slide no. CIS-7114; E, ditto, aedeagus; F, aedeagus of the paratype; G, close-up juxta of the paratype, CIS-7113; H, abdominal segments VI–VIII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529781/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
) slightly shorter than forewing; basal segment rather short, slightly dilated toward apex, dark purplish brown dorsally, pale orange ventrally; flagellum weakly bipectinate, with fine whitish cilia, dark purplish brown in basal 1/5 and pale orange in distal 4/5. Second segment of labial palpus (
<figureCitation box="[425,507,1545,1569]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,244,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,642,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-232@5.[157,1431,633,1907]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Ptilothyris galbiplatella Park, sp. nov.: A, adult, holotype; B, antenna; C, labial palpi, lateral view; D, male genitalia, gen. slide no. CIS-7114; E, ditto, aedeagus; F, aedeagus of the paratype; G, close-up juxta of the paratype, CIS-7113; H, abdominal segments VI–VIII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529781/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) thickened, pale orange all around with dark-brown scales at base; 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1239,1252,1543,1557]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">rd</superScript>
segment slender, strongly upturned, as long as 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[479,495,1579,1593]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">nd</superScript>
segment, pale orange on lateral surfaces, blackish ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1039,2037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,276,1617,1641]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">Thorax</emphasis>
: Thorax and tegula dark purplish brown ventrally. Forewing ground color purplish brown, irregularly scattered with dark-brown scales in distal part; antemedian fascia dark brown, broad, banded, from 1/3 of costa to 1/3 of inner margin; large, quadrate light yellow patch well-developed beyond antemedian fascia; costa nearly straight; apex obtuse; termen slightly oblique; fringe purplish brown; venation with R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[833,841,1741,1755]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[911,919,1741,1755]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">4</subScript>
stalked, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1033,1041,1741,1755]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">5</subScript>
absent; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1154,1162,1741,1755]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">1</subScript>
remote from R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1327,1351,1741,1755]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">3+4</subScript>
at base; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[175,183,1777,1791]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">2</subScript>
present; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[304,312,1777,1791]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">3</subScript>
, CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[375,383,1777,1791]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">1</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[485,493,1777,1791]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">2</subScript>
on a common stalk. Hind wing purplish brown, with long, more or less crescent yellowish white streak from base to 3/5 along costa; venation with M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[813,821,1813,1827]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">2</subScript>
absent; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[933,941,1813,1827]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1042,1050,1813,1827]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">1</subScript>
short stalked. Fore tibia pale orange ventrally; mid tibia dark brown ventrally, tarsi pale orange; hind tibia purplish brown on outer surface with pale orange median band and apex, pale orange on inner surface; tarsi pale orange throughout.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1039,2037]" box="[199,1335,1905,1929]" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,300,1905,1929]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[315,401,1905,1929]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,244,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,642,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-232@5.[157,1431,633,1907]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Ptilothyris galbiplatella Park, sp. nov.: A, adult, holotype; B, antenna; C, labial palpi, lateral view; D, male genitalia, gen. slide no. CIS-7114; E, ditto, aedeagus; F, aedeagus of the paratype; G, close-up juxta of the paratype, CIS-7113; H, abdominal segments VI–VIII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529781/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
): abdominal segment VIII with heavily sclerotized, C-shaped sclerite dorso-posteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1039,2037]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,607]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="595" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,357,1941,1965]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[373,446,1941,1965]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,244,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,642,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-232@5.[157,1431,633,1907]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Ptilothyris galbiplatella Park, sp. nov.: A, adult, holotype; B, antenna; C, labial palpi, lateral view; D, male genitalia, gen. slide no. CIS-7114; E, ditto, aedeagus; F, aedeagus of the paratype; G, close-up juxta of the paratype, CIS-7113; H, abdominal segments VI–VIII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529781/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="594">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
D–G): Uncus bifurcated, with broad latero-caudal lobes which are rounded apically, deeply emarginated in U-shape on caudal margin medially. Basal plate of gnathos broad, with semi-ovate expansion in middle on caudal margin; median process rather small, strongly bent from beyond 2/3. Valva elongated, nearly parallel-sided from base to distal end, with rounded apical margin; costal margin slightly concave, with weakly sclerotized marginal band; cucullus not defined from the basal part of valva, slightly upturned, densely setose. Tegumen narrowed distally, with converted V-shaped incision on anterior margin. Juxta broad, with large, membranous median plate, narrowly terminated, with pointed apex. Vinculum weakly sclerotized, banded. Aedeagus slender, bent near basal 1/3, as long as valva; cornuti consisting of a long, sclerotized bar, about 1/3 to 1/2 the length of aedeagus; the bar is located in a long sac of which the distal part is sclerotized into a triangular sclerite near apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,789,367,391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="595" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,607]" box="[199,789,367,391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="595">
<emphasis box="[199,345,367,391]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="595" reason="1">
